RIVERDANCE - 10TH ANNIVERSARY

SYNOSIS
Of all the performances to emerge from Ireland in the past decade in rock, music, theatre and films - nothing has carried the energy, the sensuality and the spectacle of Riverdance.  See Riverdance journey from its extrodinary beginnings at the Point Theatre, Dublin, with original stars Michael Flatley and Jean Butler, through its phenomenal success in Radio City Music Hall, New York to its latest live recording in Geneva. With an international cast featuring the remarkable Riverdance Irish Dance Troupe, the cream of Irish musicians in the Riverdance Band and a spectacular array of talent from Spain, Russia and America, performing to the magic of Bill Waelan&#039;s music. More electrifying that ever this DVD is a treasure for Riverdance fans worldwide.
